The paper deals with an online algorithm for buffer management, which is a classic problem in data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves linear programming and primal-dual schema, which are common techniques in optimization and information theory, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also plausible sub-categories. The paper also mentions dual fitting and multiplicative weights, which are related to approximation algorithms and game theory, respectively. Therefore, cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Approximation Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
